notesStmt.note: Whitman probably drafted this manuscript in the early 1850s as he was composing the first (1855) edition of Leaves of Grass. The lines do not have any known direct relation to Whitman's published poetry. At one point, however, the manuscript was almost certainly part of "The Great Laws do not," which includes draft lines that appeared in that edition.

note.p: These manuscript lines do not have any known direct relation to Whitman's published poetry. At one point, however, this manuscript was probably part of "The Great Laws do not," which includes draft lines that appeared in the poem later titled "A Song for Occupations."
"The Great Laws do not" also includes draft lines that appeared in the poem later titled "Who Learns My Lesson Complete?"
